author: whitlock
msg: Avoid using memset on an array of objects. Instead create a vanilla object initialised to its default values and assign each object in this array to this vanilla object.

author: whitlock
msg: when deserializing a field that's a complex array, in the code that copies the array, memset the old array to zero before deleting it, otherwise the referenced complex type's destructor will free it's strings causing AxisBench and others to fail.
